cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.CR 

This paper is about ranking measures, which are commonly used in information retrieval (IR) and machine learning (ML) applications. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.LG are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses theoretical properties of ranking measures, which could fall under cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) or cs.CR (cryptography and security). Additionally, the paper proposes a notion of "consistent distinguishability" for ranking measures, which could be relevant to cs.AI (artificial intelligence) research.
